# Maps .ai review roles to ENFORCED approvals (branch protection requires CODEOWNERS).
#
# Every @team below MUST exist as an org team with >=1 member, or GitHub treats that
# path as having no required reviewer and the rule silently FAILS OPEN (audit N5).
# Run `scripts/setup-teams.sh` to verify before flipping rulesets to 'active'.
#
# Reconciled to the org's actual teams: there is no `product` or `qa-engineer` team,
# so intake maps to `architect` and QA folds into `test-engineer`; `data-engineering`
# and `sre` are wired in. See ADR-0001 for the 2-human / 8-team gate model.

# Specs require architecture + security sign-off (Phases 2 & 3)
/docs/specs/**            @your-org/architect @your-org/security-architect
/specs/**                 @your-org/architect @your-org/security-architect
# Briefs / intake — no `product` team in the org; architect owns intake for now.
# Create a `product` team and add it here if you want a distinct product-manager gate.
/docs/briefs/**           @your-org/architect

# Code (Phase 7)
/internal/**              @your-org/backend-engineer
/cmd/**                   @your-org/backend-engineer
# Data / schema / migrations
/migrations/**            @your-org/data-engineering
/internal/**/store/**     @your-org/data-engineering
# Deploy + ops
/deploy/**                @your-org/release-engineer @your-org/sre

# Tests + verification (Phases 5 & 9; QA folds into test-engineer — no qa-engineer team)
/verification/**          @your-org/test-engineer
/**/*_test.go             @your-org/test-engineer

# Governance-sensitive surfaces
/internal/issuer/**       @your-org/security-architect
/internal/audit/**        @your-org/compliance-reviewer

# CI/deploy config + ops
/.github/**               @your-org/release-engineer @your-org/sre
